description: For sale: $1,079,900. Exquisite custom-built walk-out ranch nestled on a manicured yard! Towering, vaulted, main-floor great room with stone fireplace, built ins, maple floors and sun-filled expanses of glass!  Gourmet kitchen with 10-foot ceilings! Cherry cabinetry, breakfast bar and stainless steel appliances!  Vaulted wood ceiling in the sun/hearth room with stone floors and glass doors to a private deck! Spacious master suite with box vault, custom tile, private master bath! Main-floor office and laundry room with planning center just steps away! Walk-out level features open family/game room with custom fireplace, wet bar and glass doors to private patio area overlooking private nature preserve! Two additional generously-sized bedrooms near a full bath! Private landscaped yard with breathtaking vistas overlooking a nature preserve and just steps to a nature trail! Award-winning Wayzata Schools and easy access to downtown, Wayzata and Lake Minnetonka!

description: For sale: $449,900. Custom built home with some amazing features. This home was built for entertainment. The back yard is large, boasts an in ground pool and is very private. The formal dining room, sitting room and family room are conveniently located next to the kitchen with laundry on the main level. Going upstairs you have 2 large bedrooms with the master having a gorgeous view of the back yard and it's own deck. The loft upstairs is perfect for an office but can easily be converted to an additional bedroom with lots of storage in the walk up attic. Boasting a tandem Garage fitting 3 cars. This home has it all as the location is phenomenal and the home itself is one of a kind.

description: For sale: $334,900. With an abundance of outdoor space, this home is perfect for someone who loves a summer BBQ, drinking their morning coffee on the spacious deck, relaxing on the charming porch swing and enjoying the midwestern weather in their three-season porch. Another benefit of this home is the proximity to the Hopkins schools (within walking distance!).   Not only are there great features the new owner will enjoy outside, but the inside also offers vaulted ceilings in the living room, stone countertops in the remodeled kitchen, a gas fireplace, and a family room with a wet bar!   Are you picturing cozying up next to the fireplace with a good book or cooking your favorite meal in the kitchen? If you are, check out our 3-D virtual tour so you can explore the home even further!

For sale: $275,000. Great location close to Ridgedale and minutes to downtown Minneapolis. The main level features a spacious laundry/mud room entry from the garage making this perfect for someone seeking one-level living. The large flat backyard backs up to a pond and is complete with a fire pit and spacious deck. The walk-out lower level is the perfect set up for an in-law suite which has its own kitchen, full bathroom, bedroom, and family room. Hopkins Schools!

description: For sale: $1,359,900. Charming cottage inspired two-story blending both traditional architecture and current design trends.  Prime Minnetonka location combined with award winning Wayzata schools makes this the perfect property.  Amazing design featuring over 5500 finished square feet, including a highly desirable indoor sport court plus a 4 car garage.  Enjoy the architecturally designed kitchen, spacious open family room plus a main level office suite.  Truly unique upper level includes 5 private bedrooms or 4 with bonus room if you choose.  Beautifully designed master bedroom with luxury bath suite.  The lower level is an entertainers dream with full bar, theater room and game room, plus an additional bed and bath.  You'll appreciate all the extra details throughout this spectacular home.  Quality details abound, including beautifully finished hardwoods, large mouldings and trim, custom cabinetry throughout, top of the line Pella windows and so much more.  Rare 1/2 acre wooded lot.  Don't miss this one!

description: For sale: $1,450,000. Beautiful new construction featuring an open floor plan with versatile, light filled spaces. Luxurious finishes throughout including marble and granite counter tops and tile. Easy access to downtown,nearby business campuses, shopping and dining. Wayzata schools.

For sale: $99,900. This is a Co-op building. Nicely updated one bedroom one bath condo. This unit features wood and ceramic tile floors, stainless steel appliances, newly painted with new lighting fixtures and deck. There is an outdoor pool, BBQ area and party room. Convenient location near Oak Ridge Country Club with access to Hwy 7 and Minnetonka Blvd. Association fees include taxes, heat, AC, pool, insurance, and other standard maintenance.

For sale: $695,000. Spectacular maintenance--free villa!! This contemporary three bedroom, three bath home features high vaulted ceilings, spectacular windows and a warm neutral dcor throughout. Spacious eat-in kitchen features granite countertops, stainless appliances. Amazing main floor master with large windows and walk-in closet. The lower level includes two bedrooms, spacious family room with a wet bar. New roof and new carpet. Located in West Oaks in Minnetonka. Amenities include a pool, tennis courts, ponds and fountains.

For sale: $935,000. Extraordinary home on Huntingdon pond. Marvelous views, exceptional sprawling and sun-filled spaces and lovely finishes throughout. You'll love the large gourmet Kitchen and incredible Great Room. This home boasts 2 Master Suites with fireplaces and sitting rooms, a comfortable family room and 4-season rooms with attached greenhouse/garden room. A brand new roof was added in Dec of 2019! With over 5000 fsf, on a restful and serene location you'll enjoy being surrounded by nature and close to area shopping, parks, and trails.

Updated Chef's kitchen with granite and new premium stainless appliances.  Remodeled baths with stunning fixtures. Main level master bedroom with private bath and walk-in closet. Located in a tranquil neighborhood on a peaceful cul-de-sac. this one has it all, and is ready for a quick closing. Note, all new windows will be installed before closing.  Welcome home!

custom "Forever Barnwood", and granite counter tops. New Bosch in-unit washer and dryer and
premium GE stainless kitchen appliance package including double oven! New kitchen cabinets
with "soft close" feature. New ceramic in both baths as well and new custom shower in master.
This looks and feels like a Model Home, and it is ready for quick possession!

description: For sale: $579,000. This charming, fully remodeled home sits on a .55 acre of land in a friendly neighborhood in Minnetonka, just minutes away from parks, trails,shopping, restaurants and much more! Wayzata award winning school district. The home has 2 driveways, one to attached one car garage and one to the detached 2 car garage in the back. The home has a new beautiful kitchen and large dining area that flows into a bright living room, complete new floor plan, with added 1st floor laundry, custom wood work, hardwood floors, new plumbing, electrical, the home is fresh and has an up-to-date feel. You'll find the master suite with a luxurious bathroom on the main floor, featuring a stunning soaking tub with a walk in closet. A cozy family room, third spacious bedroom and bath is located on the lower level. Other great features in this walk-out rambler include a custom built deck and large windows

For sale: $475,000. Refreshed home w/many new updates & upgrades! New paint, white enamel trim, new carpet throughout, expanded mstr suite, updated kitchen & more! Set on quiet cul-de-sac street w/ marshland view & private backyard. Main level is light-filled with floor-to-ceiling windows and hrdwd floors in living/dining area, and views of the private backyard from the FR. Newly remodeled kit features new granite countertops & lrg granite center isl. to gather around, and a kit serving/bar area w/vaulted ceiling, new wine refrigerator, wine rack & extra sink. Upper level has 3 BR's, a convenient laundry, and a newly expanded mstr suite w/private bath & two lrg closets. LL features family room w/ wood burning frpl, 2 BR's, and exercise/office space. Lowest level is open for storage, game area or more. Backyard boasts mature trees, a privacy fence, and large entertaining deck. No showings Fridays after 7pm and on Sat's

description: For sale: $1,049,000. WOW! "Oak Ridge Villa" design on one of four, walk-out lots on scenic pond near Oak Ridge Golf Course!  Ideal main floor living with finished walkout level included.  Optional elevator.  Select your finishes! OR prefer to "custom build" on adjacent lots?  Construction commences in January, 2020.

For sale: $819,000. Stately custom built 2 bed+ office, 4 bath townhome in the rarely available & established Enclave community is being offered for the first time by the original owner. A beautiful residence that easily lives like an ultra spacious single family w/public & private living spaces on one floor. Magnificent traditional details are second to none - 10ft ceilings, 10" pegged oak hdwd flr on main, white crown molding & trim, custom wood built-ins, gourmet center island kitchen w/granite counters & high-end appliances opens to main floor family rm & paver patio. Private vaulted owner's suite overlooks treed backyard & marsh area, direct access to deck, affords a sumptuous private bath w/separate dual granite vanities, make-up station + two water closets & 5 closets (2 huge walk-ins)! Entertain in style in the LL amusement rm & wet bar. Guest bed has its own greenhouse! Storage galore incl massive cedar closet + great opportunity to customize unfinished areas. Terrific close-in Minnetonka neighborhood!

For sale: $750,000. This solid brick Minnetonka home is located on over 3 acres in a private setting. This home features Large, oversized rooms with open floor plan. Large master suite plus 2 bedrooms on main level, informal dining area with great views plus formal dining room and eat-in kitchen. Main floor also features wood burning fireplace and large laundry room. Large lower level family room + game room +2 additional bedrooms and walk out patio. And to top it off a four stall garage. Great location near Ridgedale, Target, Best Buy and only 15 minutes to downtown. Wayzata schools. New cedar shake roof installed 2017-18. New water heater & HVAC system replaced in 2018. Well landscaped grounds. Home available only due to relocation.

We have two very large decks, one completely screened in for three season enjoyment. The views are very nice, with park-like grounds, mature trees and lots of green!

The unit itself is very spacious and open. There is a nice sized kitchen with a pass-through to the dining area.  A large living room is flanked by double sliders opening up to the screened-in porch and another door with screen opening up to the east deck. The second bedroom has been converted to a comfy den with a large closet. Off of the den is a full bathroom with walk-in tub. The master bedroom is large for any condo or apartment. It has a sliding glass door opening to the screened deck.  There is a large walk-in closet. The master bath is again a full bath with linen storage.

The condo is quite and private. Greenbrier's location, just a few minutes to Ridgedale, West End and downtown, makes this a great place to live!

Recently sold: $669,900. Excellent value in a neighborhood of million dollar homes.  Beautifully private .90 acre lot w/ views of the wetlands adjoining Hilloway Park.   Tucked back on a VERY quiet cul-du-sac, this 2-Story home offers a main level owners suite, Big kitchen, formal & informal dining, family room & living room both w/ fireplaces, big laundry/mudroom and 3-car garage.  The upper level has 3 bedrooms and den & the walk-out lower level is unfinished which could add approx. 2300 additional sq. ft.  2006 Expanded kitchen renovation features custom cabinetry, big center island, granite & Silestone counter-tops, sub-zero refrigerator, built-in double oven, double drawer dishwasher, warming station for formal events.  2019-grading/landscaping in front w/ new gutters, 2018-water heater, 2017-New roof, 2011-Deck, 2009-2 New Furnaces.

description:
Recently sold: $165,000. Mkta, Free Heat, 1 HUGE Balcony and 1 Massive Deck overlooking pool, Ht Pkg

$1250 / 2br - 1240ft - 2bed/2bth, Includes heated parking, ALL UTILITIES (except electric) INCLUDING HEAT, water, sewer, etc.

Indoor and Outdoor pool (Indoor pool is heated all year long), tennis courts, workout room, party room available for rent.

The Massive deck is 34'x19' and overlooks the outdoor pool. There is also 1 HUGE balcony that run the length of the unit. Allowed to BBQ on your own balcony. This will not last! (Cedar Lake & 169).

Move in as early as April 15! 1 -2 year lease.

- Includes HEAT, heated parking, all amenities (2 pools - indoor and outdoor pool, hot tub, sauna, tennis courts, fitness room, etc) all utilities. Renter covers electric, cable, and internet.
- 2 spacious bedrooms and 2 full baths.
- 1240 sq feet
- Really quiet, awesome views of pool
- walking trails nearby
- 1 heated underground parking spot. Plenty of outside parking spaces.
- Storage Locker
- Security Deposit is equal to one months rent, application fee is $45 per adult. 
- really close to downtown, Ridgedale shopping, Uptown Lakes, Lake Minnetonka, Hopkins School

Looking for a responsible tenant.

- Air conditioning - Living room - Dining room
- Dishwasher - Refrigerator - Stove/Oven
- Microwave - Balcony, Deck, or Patio - Cable-ready
- no pets - no smoking
- Washer/dryer right down the hall

Available to view at any time. Please call or text Josh at 949-439-8425 if you are interested.
$100 move in fee payable to the Home Owners Association on move-in date

(RLNE891583)

Recently sold: $865,000. Welcome to this incredible home, nestled into a private nature setting, yet just 15 minutes to downtown! Designed and built by award winning architect Mark Kawell, this contemporary Prairie Style influenced home has a seamless flow of textures and materials. A truly sophisticated design, with a blend of natural elements and a touch of urban raw feel. A perfect home for showcasing your eclectic style, with nooks, crannies and expansive walls for artwork. An ideal floor plan for both entertaining and comfortable everyday living, with a great flow between the open yet defined spaces. The kitchen has a fireplace and large crescent shaped center island. Atrium doors lead to a dining patio with a Mugnaini Tuscan pizza oven! The lower level boasts a home theater room, exercise room and incredible 1,000+ bottle wine cellar! Outside a stone walkway leads to your private in-ground pool. Surrounded by a tall iron fence, this summertime oasis has plenty of patio spaces for relaxing and entertaining.
Recently sold: $600,000.

description: Recently sold: $585,000. Absolutely beautiful 4 bed 2.75 bath Minnetonka home! Walk-in to vaulted ceilings, multiple living areas (all with their own fireplace, 3 in total), skylights throughout the main level allow natural light to flood the home. The main living room opens into the kitchen and walks out to the backyard patio and outdoor oasis. The eat-in kitchen (with built in bench seating) is extremely bright & spacious, featuring a center island, granite counters & stainless appliances. The custom built glass display cabinets & wine bar area part of the kitchen as well. The bedrooms are very generous in size. Custom tiles in the master bathroom with dual vanities, walk-in shower & tons of storage.  Lower level is partially finished with a media room, which can be used for occasional overnight guests. Enjoy a fully screened in wood panel porch that is great for entertaining!

description:
Recently sold: $338,500. Half of a duplex for rent. I will live in the other half. They are side by side, so you won't have me stomping above you. This is the only property I own, and it is my home as well. I take pride in keeping a nice home. I will shovel, mow, etc. The home is nice. It is right off of Hopkins Crossroads. Close to highway 7, yet back in the neighborhood. Comes with in unit washer and dryer, dish washer, etc. Central heat and air. There is a separate living unit in basement, with bathroom and living room. Great for maybe an older child, or anyone who would want a little privacy. Lease duration is negotiable. The price is lower currently as it is winter, and I would like to fill it. Not reflective of the quality of the place, I honestly think it is a steal at 1900. Thinking about doing 6 month lease, then raising slightly back closer to market value (thinking just 200 bucks). You would have the right to resign before anyone else if you liked it. Please let me know if you have any questions.

Owner pays heat/electricity/water etc.

description: Recently sold: $430,000. Lovely Two-Story home in Minnetonka on a quiet cul-de-sac in desirable neighborhood of Wayzata Schools. A serene setting w/perennials, mature trees & fenced backyard. A great location with EZ access to Ridgedale, Wayzata & DT Mpls. This well maintained home is in move-in condition giving opportunity to update while keeping in value with the neighborhood homes. Recent improvements include New Roof, Gutters, LP Siding, Front Stoop & more. The main floor offers hardwood floors, walls of sun-filled windows, a spacious living room/office nook and traditional dining. The kitchen includes a breakfast area that opens to a spacious two-story great room w/brick fireplace, screened-in porch & deck. The upper level features a large master suite, vaulted ceiling, huge walk-in closet, private bath & separate shower. Additional bedrooms are ample size & share the 2nd full bath and loft area. Close to many local amenities, including the regional trail system, area parks & Lake Minnetonka.
Recently sold: $850,000.

description: Recently sold: $573,700. For more information about this property, call Leyendecker Realty at 952-388-0043. This two-story charmingly combines modern architecture and design with traditional detail and finish. The home is set on a private, maturely wooded lot in the highly desired Bent Tree neighborhood, a mile from Ridgedale and 394. The floorplan is ahead of its time with open spaces, vaulted ceilings and massive windows throughout which let in an an abundance of natural light. The kitchen features granite counters, a wall oven, expansive cabinetry storage and a large center island with seating for up to 8. The kitchen walks out to a large deck and a flat backyard. There are 3 bedrooms up including a large master suite which features a walk-in closet, a private bath with both a jetted tub and walk-in shower. The lower level has high ceilings, egress windows, a sauna, a theater room and plenty of space for entertaining. The exterior features a convenient loop driveway which connects to the oversized 3-car garage and to the uniquely covered, front entrance of the home.

description: Recently sold: $1,000,000. Welcome to 3564 Fairway Court, an art lovers dream nestled in the prestigious West Oaks neighborhood. This incredible home is protected by lush evergreens and is tucked back on a quiet cul-de-sac on a half an acre lot. The backyard is south facing and abuts the 6th green at Oak Ridge Country Club. This sprawling contemporary home features ceilings over 25 feet tall and an 80 foot long gallery-style corridor to display your art. The main level offers a grand foyer, formal living and dining rooms, a family room, and 3 bedroom suites including a spacious master. All rooms on the main level have floor-to-ceiling windows and sliding doors overlooking the private backyard. The lower level has two additional non-conforming bedroom suites (need egress windows), a wine cellar, laundry and ample storage. A large portion of the lower level is unfinished and could be used for theater, game area, storage etc.  Don't miss this rare opportunity to own a premium property in an exclusive development!

description: Recently sold: $143,500. This 2 bedroom/2 full bath east facing condo is in a quiet concrete building in a lovely complex conveniently yet privately located. Your covered balcony extends the full width of the condo and both living area and master bedroom open onto it. The master bedroom enjoys a large walk-in closet and it's own private bath/dressing area. The second bedroom can be opened to the living room if a den is preferred, as interior walls are non-supporting for any changes you choose to make. The community building is accessible to all residents until 10 p.m. to swim, work out, or enjoy a late-night sauna. It even has two guest suits for your visitors as well as a lovely community room with a fully equipped kitchen to reserve for large gatherings. Your condo is secure with underground heated parking so you'll have a warm car throughout the winter. The buildings are surrounded by open green spaces and extensive sidewalks to enjoy. There is even on-site management from 8:00am-6:00pm week days.

description: Recently sold: $685,000. Stunning updated 4bedrm walkout rambler in Wayzata school district with lovely setting, perennial gardens and pond views. Private lot with mature trees beautifully maintained.   Home has been substantially updated inside and out by current owners. Close to 394 and 494 and Ridgedale. 20 minute commute to downtown.   Part of acclaimed Wayzata School District. Neighborhood is on the steep incline with multi-million dollar homes steps away. High ceilings, beautiful pond in backyard, gorgeous gardens offer  complete privacy.  Remodel included redesign of front elevation to more updated "Hamptons" style.  New roof, complete removal of stucco exterior replaced with LP lap siding to match character and charm of new design.  Complete exterior paint. Interior paint. New hardwood floor added and existing refinished. Complete re-carpeting lower level and master. New light fixtures. Removal of many overgrown trees front and back.  Added patio firepit overlooking pond, enlarged deck to accommodate 8-person hot tub.  Home reflects elegant style of yesteryear while still offering casual easy one level living.

Relax in the lower level family room or play pool in the amusement room. Build equity by finishing off the 2 additional bedrooms and 2 bathrooms in the lower level. Plans and egress windows already started. Backs up to  walking/biking path and baseball fields. Hurry...this one will sell fast!

Recently sold: $216,000. This condominium is on the 1st floor and has a charming screened in porch off the living area of the unit. Amenities include an indoor pool, party/game room with kitchen facilities, exercise room and sauna. In addition, facility includes tennis courts, huge outdoor pool, sundeck and attractive gardens. The building is professionally managed and is very secured. It has 3 floors and a basement garage for parking and storage. This unit is assigned stall 49. Complete with lobby, elevator, mailroom St. Albans Mill condominium homes is conveniently located in a residential-park area of Minnetonka., Access is from Cedar Lake Road. Highway 494 is 1 mile west, Hwy 394 is 1 mile north and Hwy 7 is 1 mile east. This Association is governed by a Board of Directors and adheres to a set of governing documents that includes an Articles of Incorporation, Declaration, ByLaws and Rules and Regulations. Recently sold: $707,500. Take advantage of this chance to own in desirable Cedar Pass among lovely, manicured streets and higher priced homes. Original owner, two story floor plan is ready for your fresh ideas. Walk out from the main and lower levels to the sprawling backyard, perfect for summer activities. Mechanical systems have been updated so you can focus on the fun stuff by personalizing the space. Four bedrooms on the upper level plus tons of additional space in lower level with recreation room, fifth bedroom and full bath.

Recently sold: $420,000. Don't be fooled by the Minnetonka Boulevard address... this home is tucked back off the road in a small, quiet enclave of just 22 units with private and wooded backyards. Stellar finishes from head to toe include hardwood and tiled floors, custom cabinetry and mill work and updated mechanical systems. The skylights and over sized windows create sun drenched living spaces. The gourmet kitchen is perfect for entertaining and includes a huge center island with refrigerated beverage drawers, a double wall oven and expansive storage and work spaces. The master suite with heated tile floors, over sized shower with multiple shower heads and custom built vanity is your oasis from busy life. The lower level is bright and airy with a lovely guest suite, an office area and a large amusement room that walks out to the private back yard. All lovingly updated and move in ready.

description: Recently sold: $162,500. For more information about this property, call Leyendecker Realty at 952-388-0043. This 2 bedroom Cedar Ridge condo is spacious and open with large, south facing windows offering beautiful views of the maturely wooded and beautifully landscaped grounds. The unit has an open floorplan, fresh paint and carpet throughout, newer appliances and hardware, tile flooring, custom tile backsplashes, and bright, spacious bedrooms. The expansive master suite has a private bathroom with a separate vanity area, large storage cupboards and a large walk-in closet. The unit includes a storage unit just down the hall next to the coin-operated laundry room and a heated, underground, assigned parking space. Shared amenities include an indoor pool, hot tub, spa, grilling decks and a shared party room that can be rented. The condo is located in a great Minnetonka neighborhood near many coffee shops, restaurants, retail stores and has quick and easy access to Highway 169.
Recently sold: $358,000.

description: Recently sold: $207,900. Quiet, top floor, CORNER UNIT with neutral finished and lots of light! Spacious floor plan with 1 large balcony plus 1 large screen porch offering sunset views. Entire unit freshly painted, new light fixtures, new faucet, new porch carpet (July 2019). New central air conditioner (on roof) purchased 2018 which only serves Condo #321 (includes warranty). Ample storage plus large private storage closet across hall from condo, next to stairs. Underground parking stall located directly across from elevator! Lovely outdoor pool and tennis courts. Walk only 2 blocks to restaurants, coffee, happy hour, bank, grocery store! Convenient location, 2 minutes to 169 and 5 min to I-394, yet no highway noise! Only 5 to Park and Ride ramp; 6-7 minutes to Ridgedale, Target, Byerlys, Whole Foods, Trader Joe's. 2 minutes to Aldo Foods. Note: Seller will re-build wall between Bedrooms 2 and 3 upon Buyer's request in Purchase Agreement.

description: Recently sold: $425,000. One-level living in quiet neighborhood with park across the street! Open floor plan with beautiful window package for great light thru-out. Newer kitchen with 42" cabinets, granite counters, stainless steel appliances, carefree flooring. Living room with floor-to-ceiling windows for great views. French doors lead to huge family room with second of three fireplaces. Original parquet hardwoods in bedroom wing has updated bath with ceramic tile and modern vanities. Owner's suite has foyer with bonus closet storage, plus private 3/4 bath. Finished lower level has family room with fireplace, mud room, 1/4 bath and endless storage.
Recently sold: $282,600.

Recently sold: $297,500. Fantastic Minnetonka location for this 3 bedroom, 2 bath bi-level home.  So many options as the location opens the door to support your ideas and dreams.  Set on a low traffic quiet culdesac with privacy and trees, close to shopping and freeways for quick access.  Open vaulted Living Room with full wall brick fireplace.  Kitchen opens to separate dining, dinette, and 3 season screened porch.  Relax, enjoy wildlife, and the screens allow for perfect summer evenings.  THREE main floor bedrooms with TWO baths.  Most of main floor has hardwood floors!  Open canvas in lower level with fireplace and laundry hook ups.  Plenty of room to expand, renovate, or grow into the home.   Well is operable and used for outside watering.

description: Recently sold: $738,000.

Recently sold: $329,900. Charming and lovely-cared-for home set on a fabulous lot in quiet Minnetonka neighborhood. Wonderfully landscaped home welcomes you. Foyer opens the home with views of large sunlit living room and beyond to gorgeous backyard with huge deck. Living room features panoramic view from large window and cozy fireplace. This is a one of a kind 5 bed, 4 bath, 4 car garage home nestled into a cul-de-sac in a great, private Minnetonka neighborhood! This property has SO much to offer inside and out! Multiple gathering spaces throughout this home are great for hosting! The main level boasts a beautiful, formal living room, a sitting room, and a cozy family room with double sided gas fireplace, bay windows and high ceilings! The impressive, chef's kitchen has granite countertops, a double oven, hardwood floors, and it opens up to a perfect dining nook AND the kitchen walks out to the deck and pool area! The main floor also holds the laundry room and a formal dining room. The upper level features the master suite with a gas fireplace and an incredible, private full bathroom! Two more bedrooms or flex rooms and a full bath on the upper level. Lower level features another cozy family room with a fireplace and a stylish wet bar! Two bedrooms and a full bath are also on the lower level. The fenced in pool area and the maintenance free deck are a great place to spend summer days! Updates include NEW roof 2018, NEW Marvin windows 2017, composite deck 2014!

description:
Recently sold: $399,000. Coming to Market on Monday, May 20th!  Call Sharla Stafford, the Listing Agent, for info at 612-282-6895. 

This sun-filled townhome has been completely remodeled and shows like a model home. Nestled in a quiet and peaceful community, within steps of nature trails that run through the woods of Sherwood Forest on the South end of the community and wetlands of Meadow Park immediately across Plymouth Road. You will feel far away from the fast pace of the city but the commute to downtown Minneapolis is less than 15 minutes. 

Enjoy the European influenced design of the remodeled kitchen featuring hardwood floors, granite counters, modern light fixtures and enameled custom cabinetry crafted by Northland Woodworking. 

The inviting living room with hard-wood floors and a wood burning fireplace create an inviting main floor living space.  Opening to the dining room and kitchen, the floor plan is perfect for entertaining family and friends. Sliding glass doors open to two spacious decks - one off the dining room and one off the living room - offering sunny outdoor seating in both the morning and afternoon. 

Walk upstairs to the second floor and enjoy the loft with tree-top views which offers a quiet space to work or relax. There is a lovely master suite with large walk-in closet fitted with a custom closet organizer. The master bath was beautifully remodeled in 2017 with a freestanding bathtub, heated tile floors and glass-surround shower. In addition, there is a second bedroom equipped with a Queen-size Murphy Bed, perfect for accommodating overnight guests and offering great space to use as you wish when not needed as a bedroom. The adjacent full bathroom has been updated with a new vanity, fixtures and faucet. 

The lower level offers wonderful flex space, just perfect for an additional family room, office or bedroom. The sliding glass door walks out to a large patio with plenty of space for your potted plants and a small lawn. 

The freshly painted exterior, new roof, heated gutters, all new windows, four new patio doors, new water softener, water heater and air conditioner create a maintenance-free townhome for you to move in and enjoy. 

This wonderful community of 48 homes enjoys friendly and respectful neighbors, as well as a strong and well-run association. Enjoy this prime location, within walking distance of Ridgedale Mall, the YMCA, Ridgedale Library and a host of grocery stores and restaurants. 

Showings will begin on Monday, May 20th!

description: Recently sold: $830,000. Situated on Minnehaha Creek in the heart of the cities with spectacular wetland and creek views, this architecturally spectacular 4 bedroom home feels as though it were on private acreage. Custom built by SDK. Floor to ceiling glass in the soaring 2-story formal entry, elevated dining, and main level living room offers spectacular nature views. Open kitchen has an informal dining area adjacent to the rear deck and a large marble topped center island for congregating. Built in audio and video throughout, main level audio by B&W. The grand staircase leads to 3 bedrooms, all with generous walk in closets. The walkout lower level has space for entertaining with built in bar, large family room media area, and room for a pool table. Lower private office with French doors. Whole Foods is 4 blocks away, Trader Joe's and Ridgedale are 1 mile away.  There is a 2 car detached garage with room for a workbench.  The living room has nice hardwood floors and the master bedroom's hardwood floor could be refinished to like new condiition.

We bought this home about 6 years ago.  We bought the home "as-is" with a home warranty.  We are selling the home "as-is" with a 1 year home warranty.  This home was built in 1931 and we have done a some maintenance items since we bought the home.

New furnace and central AC with a wifi thermostat in fall 2013.
New gutters in 2012.
New storm door in 2012.
Painted the outside in 2012.
Tiled the shower in 2012.
New garage door in 2012.
New garage door opener in 2009.
Capped and sealed the well in 2009.  This is an old well that was capped and sealed, the home is connected to city sewer and water.

The downstairs is unfinished.  We use the downstairs as storage.  It could be finished for another bedroom or rec room or both.

The driveway does need to be replaced.  We could work the replacement into the purchase agreement.

If you are looking for a prime, flat 1 acre lot in the Wayzata school district, this is your chance.  At this price you could tear down the house and build your dream home.  The dimensions of the lot are 115x380. This is longer than a football field (including the end zones). If you drive by the property, most of the lot is behind the existing house.

description: Recently sold: $170,000. Sought after Preston Trails patio home. Spacious vaulted living room, cozy dining area, 2 generous bedrooms, all on one level. Lovely fenced patio area off vaulted living room. Easy access to major highways, Ridgedale West End and Downtown Mpls. Move right in. One year AHS Warranty included with home.

Recently sold: $137,500. 1182 square feet - 2 bed rooms and 1 3/4 bath - Recently updated, making the place look new. French Doors lead into the second bedroom / office from the living room. The fireplace is marble from floor to ceiling, and the overall appearance is very open with the recent remodel.  

This property is on a direct express route to Downtown Mpls, and is very close to the 40-mile Loop - a running, biking, and walking trail system in Minnetonka. There are also several nearby fitness centers. Please click on this link to view the running trails: http://www.eminnetonka.com/public_works/parks_trails/trails.cfm   

The property is approximately 15 minutes from down town Minneapolis, and is on the border of Minnetonka, Hopkins, and SLP.  

The Property Features a 12' x 19' master bedroom with a master bath including his and her pedestal sinks, and a mirrored 6' x 12' Walk-in Closet.  

The second Bedroom / Office is 12' x 15' and has a spacious mirrored closet.  

There are two bath rooms each styled with pedestal sinks, and mirrored cabinets.  

The kitchen is complete and sports a new dishwasher; new garbage disposal; new Microwave; & new Refrigerator.  

Utilities include: Heat, Gas, Water, Trash & Outside maintenance.  

The unit has new double pane windows, A/C; a wood burning fireplace; multiple ceiling fans; new carpet and a large 5' x 12' patio.  

Entry provides controlled Access; with an available intrusion alarm.  There is an attached and heated garage. Please note, a second spot in the heated garage is available for an extra monthly fee.  

The club house sports a complete party room equipped with a full kitchen, and is attached to the indoor pool that also includes a Spa and Hot Tub.  Just outside the clubhouse is a playground and grilling area perfect for entertaining.  For your convenience there is an extra storage unit just down the hall.  

If you have any questions, or are interested in viewing the property please do not hesitate to call. My number is 612-229-2449.

description:
Recently sold: $311,500. Rare opportunity in one of Minnetonka's most sought-after communities! 

Timeless, modern luxury condo completely remodeled features huge open floor plan with high-end custom finishes and details all-round. Dark bamboo hardwood floors with marble stonework throughout naturally create a pleasing contrast.

Gourmet kitchen invites you to entertain. Double Italian marble center islands alongside quartz counters and white cabinetry with captivating dual pantries. Beveled tile backsplash glistens against the stainless steel Samsung appliances as it travels up the chimney range hood. Cleaning is made easy with generous size sink and motion-sense touchless faucet. Natural light shines in, solarium offers sights of trees along the gentle flow of the Minnehaha creek. Make a toast! Celebrate with the built-in wine fridge, all will enjoy perfectly chilled beverages.

Impeccable master retreat boasts push button privacy with motorized window treatments while views outside are elegantly showcased by handcrafted velvet drapery. Custom-built walk-in closet and spa-like ensuite with floor to ceiling Calacatta gold marble tile from Italy.

description:
Recently sold: $209,150. Fabulous location tucked in a tree lined pocket of this quiet townhome complex.  Incredible condition, includes breakfast bar, granite counter tops throughout, new stainless steel appliances, tile flooring, fresh paint, updated lighting, and a gas fireplace.

The upstairs features a large master bedroom and a second bedroom (which can easily be used as a home office).  The master bedroom is enormous and features both a walk in closet and a reach in closet.  The full bathroom on this level has been refinished with granite and stainless bathroom fixtures.  The laundry area is also on this level, conveniently located near the bedrooms.

Townhome unit includes a patio area that is perfect for a barbecue and a patio set.

The townhome association fees are included in rental and provide water, sewer, lawn care, snow removal, and basic cable service for free!

For those that want to use public transit, MetroTransit Route 663 is an express route to downtown Minneapolis and takes 15 minutes from pickup to drop off.  The stop is just outside of the townhome edition.

The City of Minnetonka has several running and biking trails nearby.  There are a number of restaurants close to the townhome.  The West End is only 5 minutes away!  This townhome is approximately 15-20 minutes from downtown Minneapolis, and 30-35 minutes from downtown St. Paul.  It is located very close to a number of corporate business locations to include: United Health Group, General Mills, Syngenta, Target, Seimens, and Allianz.

Pet notice:  Pets are allowed in certain circumstances as allowed by the townhome association.  Dogs cannot be greater than 25lbs and must be housebroken.

This home is in the Hopkins School district.

Please call or text to setup a showing.

Includes water, sewer, garbage collection, water softer rental, and basic cable service through Comcast.

Tenant responsible for natural gas, electric, softer salt, and expanded cable or internet (if required).
